# =============================================================================
# Swift Assets V2 — Internal Cockpit — Environment template
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in real values LOCALLY ONLY.
# NEVER commit `.env.local` or any real secret to git.
#
# Only PUBLIC, browser-safe values belong in NEXT_PUBLIC_* variables.
# Service-role keys, SMTP passwords, OpenAI keys, and GitHub tokens MUST NOT
# live in this frontend app at all — they belong exclusively in Supabase
# Edge Function secrets / backend runtime (see docs/security.md).
# =============================================================================

# --- Supabase (public, browser-safe) ---
# Project: hqyktreytsjeirlpnnyr  (schema: swift_v2)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL="https://YOUR-PROJECT-ref.supabase.co"
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY="YOUR-PUBLIC-ANON-KEY"

# Base URL used to build the magic-link email redirect (auth/callback).
# Local dev: http://localhost:3000
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL="http://localhost:3000"

# Login uses Supabase email/password (signInWithPassword) — no extra env needed
# beyond the public Supabase vars above. Manage accounts/passwords in the
# Supabase Dashboard (Authentication → Users). Never hardcode a password.
# (The former TEMP_COCKPIT_ACCESS_CODE gate has been retired.)

# =============================================================================
# DO NOT ADD ANY OF THE FOLLOWING TO THIS FRONTEND APP:
#   SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY   -> backend / Edge Functions only
#   OPENAI_API_KEY              -> Edge Functions only
#   SMTP_HOST / SMTP_USER / SMTP_PASS / SMTP_FROM -> Edge Functions only
#   GITHUB_TOKEN                -> Edge Functions only
# These are listed here ONLY to document that they are intentionally absent.
# =============================================================================
